    },
    {
      "ts": "1706909830.569439",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:37:10 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "Yes, I remember you mentioning that\u2026",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706909889.617339",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:38:09 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "We would compete with Cargill\u2026I have some calls out",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706910331.577859",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:45:31 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "Crazy question to ask bunch of chemical engineers, but why in hell can you all make SESO?",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706910399.238189",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:46:39 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "Why can\u2019t we make SESO?",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706910417.930249",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:46:57 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "Humor me, why?",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706910433.918579",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:47:13 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "Well to put it in a short answer it\u2019s dangerous and highly exothermic.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706910488.475539",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:48:08 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "Like you won\u2019t have time to run away if it runs away. I have heard of horror stories from ACS ",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706910832.826069",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:53:52 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "Ok\u2026So, you can make SESO, you just don\u2019t want to make\u2026by the way, 90% of the chemistry in the industry is dangerous, exotherms, or is toxic, corrosive, etc\u2026. Just saying",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911028.866859",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:57:08 CST",
      "user_id": "U012M8NDV3K",
      "user_label": "Michael Forrester (U012M8NDV3K)",
      "text": "I'm going to expand on what Austin has said. We've never seriously considered it because of the hazards involved, but I think it could be considered. My guess though is that the cost to get a facility set up to do it would be significant. You're going to need to have lots of safety features built in.\n\nFurther, while we can and have made different epoxy contents in the lab, hitting that at scale is going to take a bit to get right. It's doable, no question, but because of how exothermic and mass transfer limited it is, you'll get several bad batches before you get good.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911060.657399",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:57:40 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "We looked at in the beginning and the hazard level was too high",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911107.480539",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:58:27 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "To make it work we would have to house 70% hydrogen peroxide in a gated off concrete area.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911121.145039",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:58:41 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "That is regulated by Homeland ",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911124.894189",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:58:44 CST",
      "user_id": "U012M8NDV3K",
      "user_label": "Michael Forrester (U012M8NDV3K)",
      "text": "Eh, I don't think you need the 70% stuff.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911141.437979",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:59:01 CST",
      "user_id": "U012212P2PQ",
      "user_label": "Austin Hohmann (U012212P2PQ)",
      "text": "ACS has to pass inspection, George told me",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911158.005709",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 15:59:18 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "I get it, had to ask\u2026.I\u2019m not making light of your comments, having been through a refinery explosion and polymer plant explosion with Unocal chemicals in the late 1980\u2026",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706911277.038049",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 16:01:17 CST",
      "user_id": "U012M8NDV3K",
      "user_label": "Michael Forrester (U012M8NDV3K)",
      "text": "I think that it's probably worth looking at some of these kinds of things again and seeing whether things have changed enough to justify it. My gut says that if we get up to a certain scale, that it may actually be worth it, but until then the risk doesn't justify it. But that's not supported by numbers, so I think that would have to happen first",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706921948.454949",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 18:59:08 CST",
      "user_id": "U0127BGJ3U5",
      "user_label": "Eric (U0127BGJ3U5)",
      "text": "Galata does epoxidation. They may be worth a reach-out. IIRC, when I talked with them a couple of years ago I got the impression they were at capacity and not eager for new stuff",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": "1706922031.000000",
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": [
        {
          "id": "F06H15U8LP4",
