        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706922324.287509",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 19:05:24 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "Agreed, who will call? ",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706922426.954359",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 19:07:06 CST",
      "user_id": "U0127BGJ3U5",
      "user_label": "Eric (U0127BGJ3U5)",
      "text": "Happy to do it /make introductions",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706922452.968069",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 19:07:32 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "Great, ",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706922457.486089",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 19:07:37 CST",
      "user_id": "U011U13BEPR",
      "user_label": "Chris Williams (U011U13BEPR)",
      "text": "Originally, we considered making SESO. But we decided at the time because of expediency to have it tolled associated with the commercial scale learning curve, cost and risk. We began with the pilot plant at the university and to say university\u2019s are risk adverse is an understatement. As the company grows, we should consider producing SESO in the the future.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1706923090.287109",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-02 19:18:10 CST",
      "user_id": "U06F97BPQJU",
      "user_label": "Jim Turner (U06F97BPQJU)",
      "text": "I\u2019ll review strategy thoughts next week\u2026a core SESO position sets up other down stream higher value PAESO products and formulations. Clearly having 3 quality and economical producers is optimal\u2026the economics to make our own SESO seems a pretty high hurdle once you dig deep enough ",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    }
  ]
